
Task
Degrees of array elements
Given an array arr. Modify the elements of the array to square each even element and each odd element to a cube.
Write a function named powerArray that takes an array arr, squares every even element, cube every odd element, and returns the modified array.
Example:
• the powerArray ([1, 2, 3, 5]) function must return [1, 4, 27, 125];
• the powerArray ([2, 4, 6, 1]) function must return [4, 16, 36, 1].

Solution
function powerArray (arr) {
for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
   if (arr [i]% 2 === 0) arr [i] = Math.pow (arr [i], 2);
   else arr [i] = Math.pow (arr [i], 3);
}
return arr;
}
